                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/31.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>580. Department’s telegram December 8. Consul, Mazatlan, telegraphs: “Tax reduced
                    two and one half per cent; time for payment extended to December 15.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
